ction of the pattern and the second integer represents the unique color.\n    The pattern is defined as a black cell followed by a cell of the unique color.\n    The unique color is the color that appears only once in the input list.\n    \"\"\"\n    color_counts = np.bincount(np.array(input).flatten())\n    unique_color = np.where(color_counts == 1)[0][0]\n    for i in range(len(input)):\n        for j in range(len(input[0])):\n            if input[i][j] == black:\n                if j < len(input[0]) - 1 and input[i][j + 1] == unique_color:\n                    return (0, unique_color)\n                elif i < len(input) - 1 and input[i + 1][j] == unique_color:\n                    return (1, unique_color)\n    return (-1, -1)", "holes": {"copy_pattern_with_unique_color": "copy the pattern according to the direction of the unique position and color them with the same color.", "find_unique_color_pattern": "find a pattern which is black and a single position which is unique color"}}
