{"action": "edit", "code": "def find_and_copy_pattern(input: List[List[int]]) -> List[List[int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Args:\n    input: A list of lists containing integers representing colors.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of lists containing integers representing colors with the pattern copied and colored.\n    \"\"\"\n    unique_color = None\n    unique_position = None\n    for i in range(len(input)):\n        for j in range(len(input[0])):\n            if input[i][j] != black:\n                if unique_color is None:\n                    unique_color = input[i][j]\n                    unique_position = (i, j)\n                else:\n                    return 'Error: More than one unique color found.'\n    if unique_color is None:\n        return 'Error: No unique color found.'\n    pattern = []\n    for i in range(len(input)):\n        row = []\n        for j in range(len(input[0])):\n            if input[i][j] == black:\n                if i < unique_position[0]:\n                    row.append(input[i + 1][j])\n                elif i > unique_position[0]:\n                    row.append(input[i - 1][j])\n                elif j < unique_position[1]:\n                    row.append(input[i][j + 1])\n                elif j > unique_position[1]:\n                    row.append(input[i][j - 1])\n            else:\n                row.append(input[i][j])\n        pattern.append(row)\n    for i in range(len(pattern)):\n        for j in range(len(pattern[0])):\n            if pattern[i][j] == black:\n                pattern[i][j] = unique_color\n    return pattern\ndef main(input):\n    output = find_and_copy_pattern(input)\n    return output", "user_code": "def main(input):\n\toutput = `find a pattern which is black and a single position which is unique color. You should copy the pattern according to the direction of the unique position and color them with the same color.`(input)\n\treturn output\n", "gpt_code": "def find_and_copy_pattern(input: List[List[int]]) -> List[